# Slack App Setup - ArgoCD Notifications

This folder contains the Slack app manifest for ArgoCD deployment notifications.

## Quick Setup

### 1. Create Slack App from Manifest

1. Go to [Slack API Apps](https://api.slack.com/apps)
2. Click **"Create New App"**
3. Select **"From an app manifest"**
4. Choose your workspace
5. Select **JSON** tab
6. Paste the contents of `argocd-notifications.manifest.json`
7. Click **"Create"**

### 2. Install App to Workspace

1. After creation, go to **"Install App"** in the sidebar
2. Click **"Install to Workspace"**
3. Select the channels for notifications:
   - `#{{ .Project.Metadata.Name }}-deployments` - Successful deployments
   - `#{{ .Project.Metadata.Name }}-alerts` - Failed syncs and health issues
4. Click **"Allow"**

### 3. Get Webhook URL

1. Go to **"Incoming Webhooks"** in the sidebar
2. Enable **"Activate Incoming Webhooks"** if not already enabled
3. Click **"Add New Webhook to Workspace"**
4. Select `#{{ .Project.Metadata.Name }}-deployments` channel
5. Copy the webhook URL

### 4. Configure ArgoCD

Create the ArgoCD notifications secret:

```bash
# Replace with your actual webhook URL
SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL="<your-slack-webhook-url>"

kubectl create secret generic argocd-notifications-secret \
  -n argocd \
  --from-literal=slack-token="${SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL}" \
  --dry-run=client -o yaml | kubectl apply -f -
```

Or add to GCP Secret Manager and use External Secrets:

```bash
# Add to GCP Secret Manager
echo -n "${SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL}" | gcloud secrets create argocd-slack-webhook \
  --data-file=- \
  --replication-policy=automatic

# The External Secrets Operator will sync it to K8s
```

## Notification Channels

| Channel                                | Purpose                  | Triggers                     |
| -------------------------------------- | ------------------------ | ---------------------------- |
| `#{{ .Project.Metadata.Name }}-deployments` | Deployment notifications | Sync succeeded, app created  |
| `#{{ .Project.Metadata.Name }}-alerts`      | Critical alerts          | Sync failed, degraded health |
| `#{{ .Project.Metadata.Name }}-prod-alerts` | Production only          | Production sync events       |

## Message Format

ArgoCD sends messages like:

```
Application {{ .Project.Metadata.Name }}-services-staging is now Synced
   Revision: abc1234
   Author: John Doe
   Message: feat: add new feature
```

```
Application {{ .Project.Metadata.Name }}-services-production sync failed
   Error: ComparisonError: Failed to compare...
```

## Testing

After setup, test the webhook:

```bash
curl -X POST -H 'Content-type: application/json' \
  --data '{"text":"ArgoCD notifications test"}' \
  "${SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL}"
```

## Troubleshooting

### Notifications not appearing

1. Check the secret exists:

   ```bash
   kubectl get secret argocd-notifications-secret -n argocd
   ```

2. Check ArgoCD notifications controller logs:

   ```bash
   kubectl logs -n argocd -l app.kubernetes.io/name=argocd-notifications-controller
   ```

3. Verify webhook URL is correct:
   ```bash
   kubectl get secret argocd-notifications-secret -n argocd -o jsonpath='{.data.slack-token}' | base64 -d
   ```

### Rate limiting

Slack has rate limits. If you're deploying frequently, consider:

- Batching notifications
- Using threading for related messages
- Limiting to important events only
